One possible contradiction lies between the testimony of Atishon and the evidence from the case details. In "Testimony 5," Atishon claims it was around 10 at night when he saw Datz Are'bal fleeing the scene, suggesting that Datz was the perpetrator fleeing after committing a crime. However, "Evidence 13: Dr. Buff's Autopsy Report" indicates the time of death was between 10 and 11 PM. If Atishon claims Datz was fleeing at 10 PM, it is possible the crime had not yet taken place, as the time of death could have been closer to 11 PM. 

This creates a contradiction between Atishon's testimony and the evidence regarding the exact timing of the crime.

